nce can\nnot be explained by the difference in mass, because the less massive star has\nmore Li. Conclusions: It is possible to achieve an abundance precision around\n$\\approx$ 0.01-0.05 dex for extremely metal-poor stars, opening new windows on\nthe study of the early chemical evolution of the Galaxy.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 10 Dec 2015 18:01:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-03-09"}
