t_c$.\nFinally, when $r$ exceeds $r_{c2}$ $\\tilde{t}$ coincides with $t_c$ and the\nphase transition becomes first order. This new mechanism indicates how the\ndiscontinuity characteristic of first order phase transitions emerges.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 11 Dec 2015 13:39:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-05-18"}
